### Relationships in the Model
READ_ME
The customer is the central component in the model. Other data components are linked to the customer to provide a more complete view for risk assessment.

The main relationships are:

- A customer is associated with a business activity
- A customer is linked to country information
- A customer has transaction summary information
- A customer has a recorded risk assessment
- A customer is connected to one or more UBOs through an ownership link
- A UBO is also linked to country information


